1. C. Rajagopalachari - He was one of the first recipients of the Bharat Ratna award in 1954, which was conferred upon him before he became the Governor of West Bengal (post-independence) and prior to his role in the Indian government.

2. Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan - He was awarded the Bharat Ratna in 1954 before becoming the first Vice President and then the second President of India. His award was in recognition of his contributions as a philosopher and academician.

3. Zakir Husain - Although not explicitly mentioned in the provided documents, it is known that Dr. Zakir Husain was awarded the Bharat Ratna before becoming the third President of India. He was honored with the award in 1963 for his educational leadership and service.

4. V. V. Giri - While not directly mentioned in the documents, former President V. V. Giri received the Bharat Ratna before becoming President, in 1975, for his contributions to the labor movement and trade unionism in India.

5. A. P. J. Abdul Kalam - He was awarded the Bharat Ratna in 1997, prior to becoming the 11th President of India in 2002. The award recognized his outstanding contributions to the fields of science and technology, particularly in the development of India's missile and nuclear programs.

These individuals were conferred with the Bharat Ratna for their exceptional service in various fields before they assumed the office of the President of India.
