1. "Miss Sara Sampson" (original spelling "Miß Sara Sampson"), a play written in 1755, is one of Gotthold Ephraim Lessing's notable works. It is considered by many scholars to be one of the first bourgeois tragedies and was Lessing's first real success as a playwright. 

